FBIS4-16096 "drsov072_b_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-072 Daily Report 14 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Deputies Deliver Protest Deputies Deliver Protest LD1404075094 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0530 GMT 14 Apr 94 LD1404075094 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Russian BFN [Text] Dissatisfied with the mild statement of the State Duma on the situation in Bosnia, approximately 20 radically inclined deputies -- Aleksandr Nevzorov, Anatoliy Lukyanov from the Russian Way group, Vyacheslav Marychev of the Liberal Democratic Party, and others -- decided to hand in their own appeal to the U.S. ambassador in Russia on Wednesday evening. Expressed in it is, and I am quoting: profound indignation at the barbaric bombing by NATO aircraft approved by President Bill Clinton. The statement also contains the demand, and I am quoting again, that: The illegal operation be investigated immediately and NATO troops be withdrawn at once from the territory of the former Yugoslavia.
